.TH HSH 1 "December 2025" "Simple Shell 1.0"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [file]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a minimal UNIX command interpreter that reads commands from
standard input or from a file and executes them. This educational
project demonstrates core shell concepts including process creation,
PATH resolution, and built-in command implementation.
.PP
The shell is implemented across tasks 0.1 through 2.1, providing
a complete basic shell experience with support for command arguments,
operators, redirection, pipes, and environment management.
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit [n]
Exit shell with status n (default 0).
.TP
.B env
Print environment variables.
.TP
.B cd [dir]
Change directory (default $HOME).
.TP
.B setenv var [value]
Set environment variable.
.TP
.B unsetenv var
Remove environment variable.
.TP
.B alias [name[='value']]
Handle command aliases.
.SH PATH HANDLING
Commands are searched in PATH directories. Commands containing '/'
execute directly. If not found: "hsh: 1: command: not found"
.SH OPERATORS
.TP
.B ;
Execute commands sequentially.
.TP
.B &&
Execute if previous command succeeds.
.TP
.B ||
Execute if previous command fails.
.TP
.B |
Pipe output between commands.
.SH REDIRECTION
.TP
.B >
Redirect stdout (overwrite).
.TP
.B >>
Redirect stdout (append).
.TP
.B <
Redirect stdin from file.
.SH VARIABLES
.TP
.B $$
Shell process ID.
.TP
.B $?
Exit status of last command.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
Interactive use:
$ ./hsh
($) ls ; pwd
($) ls | grep ".c"
($) ls > output.txt
($) cd /tmp && pwd
($) setenv TEST value
($) alias ll='ls -la'
($) exit

Non-interactive:
$ echo "ls -la" | ./hsh
$ ./hsh script.sh
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
Exit status of last command executed, or 1 on shell error.
.SH ERRORS
.TP
.B "hsh: 1: command: not found"
Command not found in PATH.
.TP
.B "hsh: line X: command: not found"
Command not found in non-interactive mode.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
Colon-separated list of directories to search for commands.
.TP
.B HOME
User home directory (used by cd).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I shell.h
Header file with function prototypes.
.TP
.I main.c
Main loop and prompt display.
.TP
.I shell.c
Command execution and PATH handling.
.TP
.I helper_functions.c
Input parsing and utilities.
.SH NOTES
This shell uses environ directly instead of getenv() for PATH
handling, as required by the project specifications.
.SH AUTHOR
Reem Abdulhadi Alshehri, Maryam Alessa
.SH PROJECT
Holberton School Simple Shell Project
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bash (1),
.BR sh (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2),
.BR wait (2)
.SH VERSION
Simple Shell 1.0
